const sections = [
  {
    title: 'The difference between SEO, local SEO, and Google Maps ranking',
    paragraphs: [
      'Many Kenyan business owners use these terms to mean the same thing, but they are slightly different layers of visibility. SEO is the work that helps your website rank in the normal organic search results. Local SEO is the branch of SEO focused on location-based searches and trust signals tied to a business area. Google Maps ranking focuses on how strongly your Google Business Profile appears inside the local pack and map results.',
      'In practice, they should not be treated as separate silos. A business that ranks organically but has a weak Google Business Profile leaves calls and direction requests on the table. A business that ranks in Maps but has a poor website can still lose the lead because the site does not convert. The strongest results come when the website, local signals, and Google Business Profile are improved together.',
    ],
  },
  {
    title: 'Why Google Maps ranking matters so much for Kenyan service businesses',
    paragraphs: [
      'For many service searches in Kenya, the Google Maps local pack appears before the normal website listings. That means people looking for a clinic, lawyer, accountant, hotel, restaurant, salon, contractor, or local supplier often make decisions from the Maps results first. Those searchers are usually ready to act. They want to call, request directions, compare reviews, or send a message quickly.',
      'That makes Maps visibility commercially powerful. If your business appears in that local pack with a strong profile, good reviews, complete details, and a clear website link, you get disproportionate attention. It is not just about traffic. It is about calls, walk-ins, WhatsApp conversations, and high-intent local enquiries.',
