    paragraphs: [
      'Your website and Google Business Profile should support the same conversion goal. The profile helps you appear in local search. The website closes the gap by explaining the service, proving credibility, and guiding the customer into a call, WhatsApp conversation, or form submission.',
      'That connection is strongest when the business name, phone number, and area served are consistent. Local schema markup, contact-page trust signals, city or area pages, and strong service descriptions all reinforce the profile. Even when the profile ranks well, a weak website can still lose the lead. Good Maps ranking without a convincing site is only half the job.',
    ],
  },
  {
    title: 'SEO and Maps ranking timeline in Kenya',
    paragraphs: [
      'Google Maps improvements can show relatively quickly for some businesses, especially when the profile is incomplete and the cleanup work is obvious. In some cases, stronger profile quality, reviews, and technical fixes can improve performance within a few weeks. Website SEO is usually slower and compounds over time, often across three to six months and beyond.',
